commitMessage:"Make ArgumentCaptor type aware (#2842)

Enhance argument captor to be more type aware. With this change it is now possible to create an argument captor that only captures certain subtypes of a parameter type.

For example:

```java
// Given:
int simpleMethod(Collection<?> arg);

// When:
mock.simpleMethod(Set.of());
mock.simpleMethod(List.of());

// Then:
ArgumentCaptor<Collection<?>> captor = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(List.class);
verify(mock).simpleMethod(captor.capture());
assertThat(captor.getAllValues()).containsExactly(List.of());
```

Fixes #565"

